# OpenShell gateway configuration overrides.
# Read by the openshell-gateway systemd --user service (EnvironmentFile).
# Symlinked into place by bootstrap/setup-host.sh:
#   ~/.config/openshell/gateway.env -> home-lab/openshell/gateway.env
#
# Contains NO secrets (driver + bind only) — committed despite the .gitignore
# *.env rule via an explicit exception. Do not put credentials here.

# Use the rootless Podman compute driver instead of the default Docker driver.
# The host already runs rootless Podman for Traefik/Portainer; the podman driver
# is purpose-built for rootless single-machine use. The Podman API socket is left
# unset so the driver uses its Linux default ($XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/podman/podman.sock),
# which keeps this file host-agnostic (no hard-coded uid). Enable the socket once:
#   systemctl --user enable --now podman.socket
OPENSHELL_DRIVERS=podman

# REQUIRED for the Podman driver: sandbox containers reach the gateway over the
# host bridge (host.containers.internal -> bridge gateway IP), not loopback, so
# the gateway must not bind to 127.0.0.1. The Debian .deb install defaults to
# loopback; the RPM/Podman default is 0.0.0.0:17670. mTLS still gates every
# connection (client cert required). Cert SANs already include
# host.containers.internal and 127.0.0.1.
OPENSHELL_BIND_ADDRESS=0.0.0.0
